  "name": "Benthic Hum",
  "mood": "Submerged",
  "engines": ["Obrix"],
  "description": "The persistent vibration of the deep ocean floor — Sine src1 (the tonal body) plus Noise src2 (sediment texture) at low mix (0.2). Journey Mode allows this hum to evolve without interruption: the drift is ultra-slow (driftRate=0.003, driftDepth=0.82) so change is geological. proc1=LP (180 Hz, low reso) keeps the noise filtered to a felt presence rather than a heard one. Four mods: Env->FilterCutoff (barely opens), LFO->Volume (breathing at 0.005 Hz), Velocity->FilterReso (pressure response), Aftertouch->Pitch (micro tuning bends). This is patient synthesis.",
  "tags": ["obrix", "submerged", "sine", "noise", "journey", "drift", "benthic", "drone", "ultra-slow"],
